title: Example for XMInt
text: Example data (exposure X, outcome Y, potential mediators M) generated follows. subject \(= 1, ..., N\): \(X_i \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1)\) \(M_{,v} = a_v X_i + e_{1_{,v}}\), \(e_{1_{,v}} \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1), v = 1, ..., V\) \(Y_i = X_i + \sum_v b_{1_{v}} M_{,v} + \sum_v b_{2_{v}} X_i \times M_{,v} + e_{2_{}}\), \(e_{2_{}} \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1)\) first three M variables (\(M_1,M_2,M_3\)) set true mediators (.e., non-zero \(\) \(b_1\) coefficients), \(X \times M_1\) set true exposure--mediator interaction term (.e., non-zero \(b_2\) coefficients), coefficients set 0. effect size (ES) represents value \(, b_1, b_2\) truth, \(a_1, a_2, a_3, b_{1_{1}}, b_{1_{2}}, b_{1_{3}}, b_{2_{1}}\) case.
code: ## data generation data = dat_gen(N = 200, V = 50, es = 1, seed = 1) X = data$X; Y = data$Y; M = data$M

title: Example for XMInt
code: ## selected mediator(s) result$selected_mediator #> [1] "M1" "M2" "M3"  ## selected interaction(s) result$selected_interaction  #> [1] "M1"

title: Simulation for XMInt
text: example simulation experiment data (exposure X, outcome Y, potential mediators M) generated follows. subject \(= 1, ..., N\): \(X_i \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1)\) \(M_{,v} = a_v X_i + e_{1_{,v}}\), \(e_{1_{,v}} \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1), v = 1, ..., V\) \(Y_i = X_i + \sum_v b_{1_{v}} M_{,v} + \sum_v b_{2_{v}} X_i \times M_{,v} + e_{2_{}}\), \(e_{2_{}} \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1)\) first three M variables (\(M_1,M_2,M_3\)) set true mediators (.e., non-zero \(\) \(b_1\) coefficients), \(X \times M_1\) set true exposure--mediator interaction term (.e., non-zero \(b_2\) coefficients), coefficients set 0. effect size (ES) represents value \(, b_1, b_2\) truth, \(a_1, a_2, a_3, b_{1_{1}}, b_{1_{2}}, b_{1_{3}}, b_{2_{1}}\) case. example, N = 200, V = 100 ES = 1, can generate example simulation experiment data using following code.
code: ## load package library(XMInt)  ## data generation data = dat_gen(N = 200, V = 50, es = 1, seed = 1) X = data$X; Y = data$Y; M = data$M

title: Simulation for XMInt
text: True mediators: \(M_1, M_2, M_3\) True exposure--mediator interaction: \(X \times M_1\) Sample size: N = 100, 200, 400 Number potential mediators: V = 50, 100, 200, 400 Effect size: ES = 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1 Number simulation runs: 100

title: Simulation for XMInt
code:
library(XMInt)  library(parallel) library(doParallel)  library(foreach)  library(iterators)   library(dplyr)   nCores <- 4 registerDoParallel(nCores)   truth_med = c("M1","M2","M3") truth_int = c("M1")    # --- simulation for N = 100 ---   N = 100 sim.times = 100 V_list = c(50,100,200,400) ES_list = c(0.25,0.5,0.75,1)  # It may take a while to run 100 simulations.  # Here we use 4 simulations to illustrate the simulation code.  N = 100;sim.times = 4;V_list = c(50,100);ES_list = c(0.5,0.75,1)  out = foreach(V = V_list,.packages = c("XMInt")) %:%   foreach(ES = ES_list) %:%    foreach(s = 1:sim.times) %dopar% {     # do simulation      cat("Case : N = ",N, ", V = ", V, ", ES = ", ES, ", Simulation = ", s, "
", sep = "")     # data      data = dat_gen(N,V,ES,seed = s)     X = data$X     Y = data$Y     M = data$M          rslt = XMInt_select(X,Y,M)     rslt   }  # list order in out: out[[V]][[ES]][[sim.times]]  # rename the list V_name_list = paste0("V",V_list) names(out) = V_name_list for (V in 1:length(V_name_list)) {   names(out[[V]]) = paste0("ES",ES_list)   for (ES in 1:length(ES_list)) {     names(out[[V]][[ES]]) = paste0("sim",1:sim.times)   } }  sim.error =    do.call(rbind,lapply(V_list, function(v){     do.call(rbind,lapply(ES_list, function(es){       do.call(rbind, lapply(1:sim.times, function(sim){         if (class(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]) == "try-error") {           re.error = data.frame(N = N, V = v, ES = es, sim = sim)         }       }))     }))   }))  # compute tpr, fdr re =    do.call(rbind,lapply(V_list, function(v){     do.call(rbind,lapply(ES_list, function(es){       do.call(rbind, lapply(1:sim.times, function(sim){         if (class(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]) == "try-error") {           out = rlist::list.remove(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]], paste0("sim",sim))         }         return(data.frame(           N = N, V = v, ES = es, sim = sim,            sim_med = paste(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_mediator, collapse = "_"),            sim_int = paste(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_interaction, collapse = "_"),             tpr_med = length(which(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_mediator %in% truth_med))/length(truth_med),            tpr_int = length(which(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_interaction %in% truth_int))/length(truth_int),            fdr_med = length(which(!out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_mediator %in% truth_med))/max(1,length(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_mediator)),            fdr_int = length(which(!out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_interaction %in% truth_int))/max(1,length(out[[paste0("V",v)]][[paste0("ES",es)]][[paste0("sim",sim)]]$selected_interaction)))           )       }))     }))   }))  # save results if (is.null(sim.error)) {re_N100 = re} else {   sim.error = sim.error %>% as.data.frame() %>% mutate(id = paste(N,V,ES,sim,sep = "_"))   re_N100 = re %>% mutate(id = paste(N,V,ES,sim,sep = "_")) %>% filter(!id %in% sim.error$id) %>% select(-id) }    # --- simulation for N = 200 ---   N = 200 sim.times = 100 V_list = c(50,100,200,400) ES_list = c(0.25,0.5,0.75,1)  # To illustrate simulation code, use 4 simulations N = 200;sim.times = 4;V_list = c(50,100);ES_list = c(0.5,0.75,1)  out = foreach(V = V_list,.packages = c("XMInt")) %:%   foreach(ES = ES_list) %:%    foreach(s = 1:sim.times) %dopar% {     # title: Data generation function — dat_gen
text: function generates simulation data (exposure X, outcome Y, potential mediators M). subject = 1, ..., N: \(X_i \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1)\) \(M_{,v} = a_v X_i + e_{1_{,v}}\), \(e_{1_{,v}} \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1), v = 1, ..., V\) \(Y_i = X_i + \sum_v b_{1_{v}} M_{,v} + \sum_v b_{2_{v}} X_i \times M_{,v} + e_{2_{}}\), \(e_{2_{}} \stackrel{..d}{\sim} N(0, 1)\) first three M variables (M1,M2,M3) set true mediators (.e., non-zero b_1 coefficients), X x M1 set true exposure--mediator interaction term (.e., non-zero b_2 coefficients), coefficients set 0.

title: Data generation function — dat_gen
text: N sample size V number potential mediators es effect size, representing value , b1, b2 truth seed seed. Default 1234.

title: Data generation function — dat_gen

title: Model estimation — model_estimate
code: model_estimate(   X,   M,   Y,   I_update,   tol = 10^(-10),   max.iter = 10,   lambda1 = exp(1),   lambda2 = exp(-1),   alpha = 1,   penalty.factor = c(1, rep(1, ncol(M) * 2), rep(1, max(0, ncol(I_update)))),   verbose = FALSE,   Omega.out = FALSE )

title: Model estimation — model_estimate
text: X one-dimensional exposure M multivariate mediators Y one-dimensional outcome I_update interaction term tol convergence criterion (default = -10^(-10)) max.iter maximum iteration (default = 10) lambda1 tuning parameter regression coefficient L1 penalization lambda2 tuning parameter covariance-inverse matrix alpha alpha glmnet() (default = 1: lasso penalty) penalty.factor penalty factor vector, order (c,b1,b2,) verbose print progress (default = FALSE) Omega.output Omega estimates (default = FALSE)

title: Model estimation — model_estimate
text: c: direct effect estimate hatb1: path b1 (M->Y given X) estimates hatb2: path b2 (X*M->Y) estimates hata: path (X->M) estimates nump: number selected paths + 1 direct effect Omega: estimated covariance-inverse matrix mediators sigmasq: estimated variance outcome
